items.description: Pandavleni Caves, also known as Pandu caves or Nasik Caves, are situated in the foothills of Trivashmi Hills and are ancient rock-cut caves. Known to be built around the 3rd century, the caves are a combined group of 24 caves that represent Hinayana Buddhism. The caves are beautifully carved and there are inscriptions inside and outside the cave that not only acts as study material for scholars but the intricacies are amazing to look at. Visiting these caves are one of the many things to do in Nashik.

items.description: Soma Vine Village in Nashik is famous for its extensive vineyards which are overlooked by a pristine environment. Here you can take part in a grape stomping activity with your friends, family, or loved ones and make beautiful memories. Freshly plucked grapes are stomped upon in large barrels wherein you are required to be barefooted. You are also required to clean your feet before indulging in this activity. The activity promises infinite fun and laughter and a never-before experience along with wine tasting after the stomping activity making it one of the most love-filled things to do in Nashik.
